&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS A FIXED TERM CONTRACT FOR 3 MONTHS TO COVER SERVICE NEEDS.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mass Vaccination Programme in Gwent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a key member of the team, you will be required to work across the Gwent wide area, supporting the Mass Vaccination Programme within any one our community venues including mobile units.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide general administrative and clerical support to the Mass Vaccination Programme Team, acting as point of contact for a variety of stakeholders, both internal and external ranging from members of the public to senior personnel at one of the sites in Gwent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be a motivated, and be a team player who is able to meet the geographical needs of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 18th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
